## ⚡ Electricity – Pacific Gas & Electric Company (PG&E)
**Description:** Pacific Gas & Electric Company (PG&E) provides natural gas and electricity to most of the northern two-thirds of California, including San Jose. They are committed to delivering safe, reliable, and affordable energy to their customers.

**Contact Info:**  
- **Phone:** 1-800-743-5000  
- **Website:** [pge.com](https://www.pge.com/en.html)  
- **Email:** Not specified  
- **Address:** 77 Beale Street, San Francisco, CA 94105  

**Emergency Steps:**  
- Call 9-1-1 immediately to report any downed powerlines.  
- If you are in a vehicle that is in contact with a downed powerline, keep your hands at your sides and jump clear of the vehicle. Ensure you are not touching the vehicle when your feet hit the ground.  
- Once you are clear of the vehicle, keep your feet close together and shuffle away from the vehicle without losing contact with the ground to avoid electric shock.  
- Do not attempt to touch or move downed powerlines or anything in contact with them.  
- Ensure that any generators you use are not connected to PG&E’s power lines to prevent back feeding, which can endanger utility workers and damage property ([pgealerts.alerts.pge.com](https://pgealerts.alerts.pge.com/safety/electricity/)).